tweet: If I had to say something bad about @MissMarisRacal's #Stellar, it would be that I think it's bitin. I honestly don't understand the trend of releasing albums with just a handful of new songs. Am I the only one who loves Maris' songwriting so much that I'd kill for a 20-song set?

Hi, MarNigo fam! I just listened to @MissMarisRacal's #Stellar from beginning to end. It's a very well-crafted song cycle with tracks about the heady rush of an all-consuming crush, not knowing where you stand with someone, and how tough it is to fall in love in the public eye.

Anyway, congrats, my dear @MissMarisRacal! #Stellar is definitely among my top OPM albums of 2018. MarNigo fam, she made us all really proud with this album, didn't she? Now, excuse me while I figure out how to cover "Ikaw Lang Sapat Na" for IGTV or YouTube. Hehe.

Fun fact: the only song @MissMarisRacal didn't have a hand in writing on #Stellar is "Hi Crush," which was composed by @406Unit frontman Gabriel Tagadtad, who I believe wrote the rap on @ImPascualInigo's "Dahil Sa 'Yo." Speaking of Inigo, RT if you floved "Tayo Na 'di Tayo!"

.@MissMarisRacal wrote most of the album by herself, which is why listening to it feels like a peek into a close friend's private diary. The earnest way Maris sings all the songs adds to #Stellar's intimate vibe. I feel like I know her even better after I played the album.
Love is Easy is definitely my favorite. #Stellar
